any thing i should do with my yorkie puppy right away other than medical things like taking it to the vet is there any thing else you would do after buying a week old yorkie answers make sure you are using the right housebreaking techniques play with his her feet every day and at four months after the final rabies and distemper vaccines set up a grooming appointment for your puppy yorkies need proper grooming and should be maintained every weeks the earlier you start with the grooming process the less afraid and stressed your baby will be interview groomers in your area and find a groomer you can trust ask you vet if he recommends anyone specifically i mentioned playing with the feet because sometimes yorkies do not like their nails being cut also even though he she might not have a lot of hair invest in a good slicker brush and comb to keep you dog mat free Housebreaking Rabies Dog training Pet skunk Dog Ferret Socialization Yorkshire Terrier Shetland Sheepdog Guinea pig Brush Keeshond My Little Pony Breastfeeding Investigation into the bombing of Pan Am Flight 103 Skinny Puppy Havanese The Ashlee Simpson Show Certified Nursing Assistant Cat First aid Past teachings of Prem Rawat Francis Bacon (painter) Skiing American Eskimo Dog Nail (anatomy) Fancy rat Blue Peter Upholstery Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Docking Textile manufacturing Dreadlocks Eastern Orthodox Church Portuguese Water Dog Social rule Road Rovers Current teachings of Prem Rawat Jennifer Lopez Sabbath Nestl__ Milton H. Erickson Garfield Scientology beliefs and practices Antiviral drug Beethoven (film) Microeconomics Spotted Skunk Phoebe Buffay's songs Childbirth Empire Burlesque Mixed-breed dog Cancer Dennis the Menace (UK) Sampling (music) Skye Terrier Crate training Rastafari movement Maltese (dog) Plame affair Dobermann Airedale Terrier Reflexology Richard Chase Tooth Abortion Yami to B__shi to Hon no Tabibito Economics Basset Hound Final Fantasy Tactics Advance Kodocha Livestock Paranoia Agent Pek